From: Cris7015 <pcristian292@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] of: net: support mac-address-increment(-byte)

The cjdelisle econet 6.12 tree lacks OpenWrt of_get_mac_address support
for mac-address-increment / mac-address-increment-byte. Add it so per-radio
MACs can be derived from a single base MAC in flash (used by the XR500v
MT7603 2.4GHz radio: base 0xf100 + 1).

Signed-off-by: Cris7015 <pcristian292@gmail.com>
--- a/net/core/of_net.c
+++ b/net/core/of_net.c
@@ -168,6 +168,17 @@
 		return ret;
 
 found:
+	{
+		u32 inc_idx = 5;
+		u32 mac_inc = 0;
+
+		of_property_read_u32(np, "mac-address-increment-byte", &inc_idx);
+		if (inc_idx > 5)
+			inc_idx = 5;
+		of_property_read_u32(np, "mac-address-increment", &mac_inc);
+		if (mac_inc)
+			addr[inc_idx] += mac_inc;
+	}
 	ret = of_add_mac_address(np, addr);
 	return ret;
 }
